@JasonFengJ9 I would rather the callers of the Lookup ctors made an explicit choice to either pass the default or set the as required for their call.
A method that passes thru and drops the argument is confusing and makes the code harder to reason about.
This method should be to get the default for the release - that's why it has Default in it's name :)
private static boolean lookupJLIPackageCheckDefault()

